{"type":"text","timestamp":1773433470208,"sessionID":"ses_31723c315ffeTdWKv3RfQTSDr6","part":{"id":"prt_ce8df17bf001ec5rsUGOb9eaEE","sessionID":"ses_31723c315ffeTdWKv3RfQTSDr6","messageID":"msg_ce8df0ee1001qKhEgIvyQr1tCy","type":"text","text":"The implementation is complete. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n## `src/lib/test-detection.ts` — Test Detection Module\n\n### Types & Interfaces\n- **`DiffFile`** — Represents a file from git diff with status (A/M) and path\n- **`SourceFileTestInfo`** — Per-source-file test analysis result\n- **`TestDetectionReport`** — Overall report with coverage metrics\n- **`TestDetectionConfig`** — Configurable patterns for test detection\n\n### Core Functions\n\n1. **`getChangedFiles(projectRoot, compareRef)`** — Parses `git diff --name-status` to find added/modified files. Handles edge cases (first commit, missing ref) with graceful fallbacks.\n\n2. **`filterSourceFiles(files, config)`** — Filters diff output to only source files in configured directories, excluding test files themselves.\n\n3. **`isExcludedFile(filePath, projectRoot, config)`** — Checks if a file should be excluded from test requirements:\n   - `*.d.ts` type declaration files\n   - `index.ts` re-export barrels (detected via content analysis)\n   - Types-only files (only type/interface/enum declarations)\n   - Custom exclude patterns from config\n\n4. **`isBarrelFile(absPath)`** — Analyzes file content to determine if it's a re-export barrel.\n\n5. **`isTypesOnlyFile(absPath)`** — Analyzes file content to detect types-only files with no runtime code.\n\n6. **`findTestFiles(sourcePath, projectRoot, config)`** — Searches for corresponding test files using multiple strategies (flat, mirrored, co-located) and recursive directory scanning.\n\n7. **`detectTests(projectRoot, compareRef, config)`** — Main entry point that orchestrates the full analysis and returns a structured `TestDetectionReport`.\n\n8. **`renderTestDetectionReport(report)`** — Human-readable text output for CLI.\n\n### Build Verification\n- ✅ TypeScript typecheck passes\n- ✅ Build succeeds (bundled 150 modules)","time":{"start":1773433470205,"end":1773433470205}}}
